README for test/GCClassic (GEOS-Chem integration test directory)
09 Nov 2020
GEOS-Chem Support Team
geos-chem-support@g.harvard.edu
===============================================================================

Overview:
---------

This directory contains scripts to submit automated GCClassic integration
tests, which will test the following process:

1. GCHPctm run directory creation
2. GCHPctm code configuration and compilation
3. GCHPctm execution

Integration tests are mostly intended to be run by GEOS-Chem developers,
rather than end users.


Files:
------
intTest_slurm.sh        : Driver script to set up GCHPctm integration test
intTestCreate.sh        : Script to create GCHPctm run directories
intTestCompile_slurm.sh : Script to compile GCHPctm
intTestExecute_slurm.sh : Script to run GCHPctm 
gchp_benchmark.slurm.sh : Run script for GCHPctm benchmark simulation (SLURM)
gchp.lsf.sh*            : Run script for other GCHPctm simulations (LSF)
gchp.slurm.sh*          : Run script for other GCHPctm simulations (SLURM)


Running integration tests with the SLURM scheduler:
---------------------------------------------------
Execute the following commands at the Unix prompt:

  cd test/GCClassic
  ./intTest_slurm.sh /path/to/int/test/dir GCHP-ENVIRONMENT-FILE


Running integration tests with the LSF scheduler:
--------------------------------------------------
Execute the following commands at the Unix prompt:

  cd test/GCClassic
  ./intTest_lsf.sh /path/to/int/test/dir GCHP-ENVIRONMENT-FILE





